<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Multimedia Player</title>
</head>

  <h1>My Media Player</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Song Playing</h2>

    <audio controls aria-label="Song Playing">
      <source
        src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/js-music-player/sailing-away.mp3"
        type="audio/mpeg">
      Your browser does not support the audio element.
    </audio>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Video Playing</h2>

    <video
      controls
      width="600"
      aria-label="Video Playing">

      <source
        src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/labs/what-is-the-map-method-and-how-does-it-work.mp4"
        type="video/mp4">

      <track
        src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/labs/what-is-the-map-method-and-how-does-it-work.vtt"
        kind="subtitles"
        srclang="en"
        label="English">

      Your browser does not support the video element.
    </video>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Transcript</h2>

    <p>
      This video explains what the JavaScript map() method is, how it works,
      and demonstrates practical examples of using it to transform arrays.
    </p>
  </section>

